'''Alberto de Angelis''' (born 1885) was an Italian writer mostly remembered for writing a biography of [[Domenico Mustafà]], entitled ''Domenico Mustafa – La Cappella Sistina e la Società Musicale Romana''.

The book was published in 1926, and is considered of significant importance for its valuable account of Mustafa's life, the musical society in Rome and the other [[castrato singer|castrati singers]] at the [[Capella Sistina]].

